an> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">Carol Polsgrove (2009). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=ROotAQAAIAAJ\"><i>Ending British Rule in Africa: Writers in a Common Cause</i></a>. Manchester University Press. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-7190-7767-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-7190-7767-8\">978-0-7190-7767-8</a><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">30 October</span> 2012</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=Ending+British+Rule+in+Africa%3A+Writers+in+a+Common+Cause&amp;rft.pub=Manchester+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-7190-7767-8&amp;rft.au=Carol+Polsgrove&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DROotAQAAIAAJ&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ADorothy+Pizer\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/wiki/Cameron_Duodu\" title=\"Cameron Duodu\">Cameron Duodu</a>, <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.pambazuka.org/en/category/features/74465\">\"George Padmore commemorated with plaque in London\"</a>, <i>Pambazuka News</i>, Issue 537, 30 June 2011.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Smith2012-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-Smith2012_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\">S. Shankar (31 January 2012). \"Colonial Politics and the Travel Narrative\".  In Virginia Whatley Smith. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=ue_cBbnEahIC&amp;pg=PA15\"><i>Richard Wright's Travel 